title: For Sale:  West German sig p226 complete For parts
postcontent:
Long story short, I have owned this West German made sig for a long time. I dropped it off to have it cerakoted and the smith fucked it up. The magazine release has a small spring loaded pin that needs to be depressed before being taken apart. He obviously took a punch to it and knocked out the tiny part of the frame it grabs onto. I then had the area rewelded but it was too soft and the release worked itself out. It still functions flawlessly and worked great for several hundred rounds before the weld failed.

Its a shame since its getting harder to find W. German made sigs and this one was a nice one. Has a trigger job and newer spring kit installed last couple years. I even used it a couple times in IDPA at the Master level. 

I think my asking price is pretty fair considering what I have seen just the complete slide/barrel and original grips sell for. Use it for parts or if you have a competent smith they can very easily fix this. I just recently acquired a mk25 and x5 so I have decided not to pursue repairing this one. 

$400 or may trade towards a 238 or 938 with extra cash on my part.

title: For Sale/Trade:  AR15 .223 Rifle
postcontent:
Thank you for everybody that has expressed interest in this rifle over the last month or so. I apprecaite your offers, and feedback. I have revised the  listing, added a couple items that were missing before, and do have ammo i can add to this package. Please read carefully, and ask any questions you have. i have tried to cover any issues, questions, or offers that i have came  across. 

For those of you who are skeptical of the Poly lower, watch this video. it helped me decide to purchase it. 
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_qpnmi3XPP8&feature=player_embedded

This is a personally built rifle with the following major parts: - New Frontier Poly lower and parts kit (110.00) - UTG 6 position stock (30.00) - Sota Arms Upper (130.00) - Sota Arms Floating Guard (30.00) - JoeBobs premium Bolt Carrier Group (155.00) - (2)30 round poly magazines (40.00) - Bulldog AR15 hard/soft case (55.00) - Sota Arms 16inch Stainless M4 Barrel (150.00) - Forward grip with extracting bipod (20.00) - Reactive site with multiple settings (30.00) - AR15 multipurpose wrench (10.00) - Muzzle Brake (40.00)

purchased and assembled bit by bit. took it to the range and had a gunsmith check it over, he did the following: - replaced the poly trigger/hammer. - adjusted the gas block and buffer/stock - installed detents 

We tested with the poly magazines, The rifle hated the poly magazines, it would not reload after 2-3 rounds. We used a steel magazine and it was flawless, put 50 rounds through nice and smooth and no other hiccups. havnt had it out since then. 

So, you will need quality magazines, i will include the poly, but they are pretty much useless. I dont think we tested both mags, it is possible that one of the mags will work fine, but i cant remember if we did, so i wouldnt count on it.

I enjoyed putting this together, but my tastes change and need to fund a new hobby. :)
